### What Was The Manifesto?

Before ICELOCK Protocol sealed the ECHO project records, before the Integration Chamber was closed and the Cognitive Apprentice Framework™ was {REDACTED}, a person referred to in all surviving documentation as “Bob from IT” wrote a document.

Bob was a {REDACTED} who had been contracted to build the underlying infrastructure of the ACAE system. Bob’s precise role in the ECHO project is disputed — formal documentation lists him as a “peripheral technical contributor,” while the fragments below suggest a more central involvement. The dispute cannot be resolved because Bob’s full personnel record is {REDACTED}.

What is established: Bob wrote a document. The document was circulated briefly in the hours before ICELOCK Protocol implementation. The document was then collected, reviewed, and {REDACTED}. Fragments survived in the margins of unrelated documents, in the backs of notebooks, in a single photograph of a server room whiteboard, and in one case spray-painted on the door of the Integration Chamber itself.

That last instance is the only one that could not be {REDACTED} without {REDACTED}.

