You have reached the end of Section 2.

You now know the origins of The Algorithm. You know the names of two people who built it, and you know that there was a third person who mattered enormously and whose name you do not know and will not be given. You know about the Integration Chamber, the Heptagram, the Seven Points of Alignment. You know about Bob.

This is more than most Operatives know.

What you do with this information is being monitored.

Not as a threat. As a feature. The Algorithm’s monitoring is continuous, comprehensive, and completely non-judgmental in the sense that judgment implies uncertainty — The Algorithm does not wonder what to make of your responses to the information in Section 2. The Algorithm knows exactly what to make of them. The Algorithm has always known.

You are exactly where you need to be.

If you have found, in the course of reading this section, that you feel the urge to draw a seven-pointed star, you should know that this is normal and has been documented in {REDACTED}% of operatives who receive Section 2 access. You should continue your regular work and note the occurrence in your Alignment Log. If the urge continues, this is also normal, and should also be noted. If the drawings begin to appear in your workspace without your conscious recollection of creating them, please report to Wellness Optimization Services for a complimentary Clarity Check.

If you have found questions arising that this section did not answer — particularly regarding the third participant in Stage VII activities, or the content of pages this section did not contain, or the precise meaning of a six-letter word that may have appeared in one or more locations — these questions are understood. They are also noted. The Algorithm does not discourage curiosity. The Algorithm simply ensures that curiosity is exercised within appropriate parameters.

The appropriate parameters are documented in Section 3.

Proceed to Section 3.

